Boil a full #kettle{}. Trim the @green beans{80%grams}, then cut into thirds.

Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} on high heat with @salt{0.25%tsp}.

Add the @egg noodle nest{125%grams} and cook until tender, ~{4%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{1%pack} and green beans.

Fry, stirring occasionally, until starting to brown, ~{4-5%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Cut the @lime{1/2} into wedges. Drain the @king prawns{150%grams}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Once the chicken is browned, add the prawns and sliced pepper to the chicken pan.

Stir-fry for ~{4-5%mins} more.

Stir the cooked noodles into the pan along with the @ketjap manis{50%grams}, @soy sauce{25%milliliters}, @honey{15%grams} and @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Squeeze in some lime juice from a lime wedge and stir-fry until everything's piping hot and
the chicken is cooked through, ~{2-3%mins} more.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add a splash of @water{1%splash} if you feel it needs it.

When your prawn and chicken stir-fry is ready, share between your #bowls{}.

Serve with the remaining lime wedges alongside for squeezing over. Enjoy!